<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 05 at 1:56AM CDT until May 05 at 2:15AM CDT by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 215 AM CDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN CARROLL COUNTY...
At 156 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Grandview,
moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations in or near the path include...
Berryville...                     Eureka Springs...
Beaver...                         Urbanette...
Grandview...                      Pleasant Ridge...
Oak Hill...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
